                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            <seg type="para">This fragment is a single folio, taken probably from an Oktoechos,
                                containing the <title>Stichera martyrika</title>, a hymn sung during the morning 
                                office (<hi rend="italic">orthros</hi>), in alternation with a psalm or scriptural verses (<hi rend="italic">stichoi</hi>).</seg>
                            <seg type="para">The fragment was acquired by Constantin von Tischendorf 
                                and bought from his heirs by Cambridge University Library in 1876.</seg>
                            <seg type="para">Dr Matteo Di Franco</seg>
                        </summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="grc">Greek</textLang>

                        <msItem n="1">
                            <!--<locus from="1r" to="1v">f. 1r-1v</locus>-->
                            <title xml:lang="eng">Stichera Martyrika (fragment)</title>
                            <incipit defective="true">
                        <locus from="1r" to="1r">f. 1r</locus>
                                ἔχοντες οἱ ἅγιοι περιβολὴν <supplied>ἐν</supplied> τῶ κόσμω· τὰς βασάνους 
                                <supplied>τῶν ἀν</supplied>όμων ὑπέμειναν· καὶ 
                                <supplied>τὴν</supplied> πλάνην τῶν εἰδώλων</incipit>
                            <explicit defective="true">
                        <locus from="1v" to="1v">f. 1v</locus>
                                Λάμπει σή<supplied>μερον ἡ μνήμη</supplied> τῶν ἀθλοφόρων· <supplied>ἔχει γὰρ</supplied> 
                                καὶ οὐρανόθεν <supplied>ἀπαύγασμα,</supplied> ὁ χορός τῶν ἀγγέλων πανηγυρίζει· 
                                καὶ τῶν ἀνθρώπων τὸ γένος συνεορτάζει· 
                                <supplied>ταῖς ἁγίαις αὐ</supplied>τῶν πρεσβίαις Χρίστε <supplied>ὁ Θεὸς, ἐλέ</supplied>ησον ἡμᾶς.
                                Μαρτθρικόν ἦχος <gap/> φῶς δικαίοις διὰ παν<supplied>τὸς</supplied> 
                        <gap/> τε <gap/> φασ<gap/> σβέσαντες ὧ<gap/>
                     </explicit>
                        </msItem>
                        
                    </msContents>

