                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote scope="sole" xml:id="hand-1">
                                <p>The text has been copied in a calligraphic <term type="script">Hodegon-style mixed minuscule</term> script,
                                    with variable slant, in brown ink. 
                                    There is moderate variation in letter size.</p>
                                <p>Syllabic abbreviations and superscript word endings are in use 
                                    in the ending of lines.
                                    Breathings are curved, mute <hi rend="italic">iota</hi> is
                                    absent, with frequent decorative use of the double dot on <hi rend="italic">ypsilon</hi> 
                                    and accentuation of all <hi rend="italic">nomina sacra</hi>.</p> 
                                <p>The modern <hi rend="italic">eta</hi>, <hi rend="italic">sigma telikon</hi> and loop <hi rend="italic">epsilon</hi> are present. The <hi rend="italic">beta</hi>
                                is mostly in u-shape.</p>
                                <p>Punctuation used includes the middle and upper points, 
                                    lower commas and full stop.</p>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>

                        <additions>
                            <p>In outer margin of the <locus from="1v" to="1v">verso</locus> a sketch of a sailing boat has been drawn 
                                by a reader, along with some other scribbles.</p>
                            <p>A modern hand has added the current classmark and former classmark "T.24" on the upper margin.</p>
                  </additions>
                        
